 LOOSE CHANGE

																								 The Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation Ltd (IRCTC) plans to optimise resources to cater to the needs of the budget traveller by using unused train coaches. The corporation is in talks with Indian Railways to offer budget travel packages. The Bangalore division of South Western Railway has agreed to offer coaches to IRCTC for use as part of weekend tour packages. Outbound packages to popular destinations such as Shirdi, Goa and Hampi are being planned. A similar arrangement with IRCTC-Bhubaneswar is also in the offing to attract inward tourists to Bangalore, Mysore, Hassan, Coorg and Ooty from Bhubaneswar. 
																								 Birla Sun Life Insurance Company has launched Saral Jeevan, in which the risk cover starts as soon as the policy is bought. Any person in the age group of 18 to 55 years can simply fill the application form, agree to three health-related statements and buy the policy by submitting required documents such as identity, income and residence proof, and the premium. 
																								 Reliance Mutual Fund has announced a dividend under the quarterly dividend option of Reliance Medium Term Fund and Reliance Monthly Income Plan. The record date for the same is December 20. 

